The idea:
Click a point to define 2 coordinates

1: GENERIC NAME of POINTS
   To define a GENERIC NAME which will be concatened
   to the number of generation
   Example : P => P1 P2 P3 ...

2: NAME of the MAPPING of the POINTS
   If the MAPPING is different of I, all input points
   will be transported by this mapping.

   The MINIMUM and MAXIMUM of the INPUT FRAME for the
   clicked points may be done by
3: ABSCISSE MIN MAX & STEP of FRAME for the X abscisses
4: ORDINATE MIN MAX & STEP of FRAME for the Y ordinates

5: 3 POINTS define the PLAN of POINTS
   3 POINTS P1 P2 P3 define the input plane
   The POINT P1 is the new origin of the input plane
   The direction P1-P2 define the X-axis.
   The direction Z is defined by P1P2 x P1P3
   The direction Y is defined by Z x X.

6: PLANE of POINTS at X=Constant
   The input plane will be YZ.
   The third coordinate Z of clicked points will be 
   the input value done after.
  
7: PLANE of POINTS at Y=Constant
   The input plane will be XZ.
   The second coordinate Y of clicked points will be 
   the input value done after.

8: PLANE of POINTS at Z=Constant
   The input plane will be XY.
   The third coordinate Z of clicked points will be 
   the input value done after.

9: NO PLANE of POINTS
   SUPPRESSION of all previous options

20: the input by ckicking of points may begin...
    Move the mouse
    Click to define 2 coordinates
    ...

A menu appears and may be used:

  DELETE a POINT : To delete a point
   Move the mouse in the rectangle DELETE a POINT and click
   Move the mouse in the vicinity of a point and click
   => the point disappears

  X-ATTRACTION:   
   Move the mouse in the rectangle X-ATTRACTION and click.
   Every future clicked point will be projected on the
   nearest X-graduation
 
  NO X-ATTRACTION:   
   Move the mouse in the rectangle NO X-ATTRACTION and click.
   Every future clicked point will NOT be projected on the
   nearest X-graduation. The X of the click will NOT be modified.

  Y-ATTRACTION:   
   Move the mouse in the rectangle Y-ATTRACTION and click.
   Every future clicked point will be projected on the
   nearest Y-graduation
 
  NO Y-ATTRACTION:   
   Move the mouse in the rectangle NO Y-ATTRACTION and click.
   Every future clicked point will NOT be projected on the
   nearest Y-graduation. The Y of the click will NOT be modified.

  ESCAPE: To abandon the clicking of points
   Move the mouse in the rectangle ESCAPE and click.
   The execution return of one level in the menu tree.
